The concert DVD features some of the last known footage 
taken of Tupac before his death by multiple gun shot wounds 
in 1996. The live performance, captured from Los Angeles on 
July 4th, will include an uncensored portrait of Shakur&#039;s 
live show, as well as performances by the Outlawz and also 
Snoop Dogg. There are also several music videos featured plus
an exclusive interview with the head of Death Row records Suge 
Knight. This DVD captures Tupac at the peak of his career and 
is a must have for all his fans.
